or ‭‬  important notice information for clients of butterfield bank uk limited learn more    content editor ‭‬  ​   legal security  privacy  butterfield  butterfield bank  wikipedia butterfield bank from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search butterfield type public traded as bsx ntbbh founded  headquarters hamilton bermuda area served bahamas bermuda cayman islands guernsey switzerland united kingdom products banking butterfield officially the bank of n t butterfield  son limited is a bank founded and based in bermuda butterfield offers a full range of community banking services in bermuda and the cayman islands encompassing retail and corporate banking and treasury activities butterfield also provides private banking asset management and personal trust services from its headquarters in bermuda and subsidiary offices in the cayman islands guernsey and the united kingdom in switzerland and the bahamas butterfield provides personal trust and company services it is listed on the bermuda stock exchange bsx historyedit butterfield bank in george town grand cayman it grew out of a bermuda trading company founded by nathaniel butterfield in  butterfields son nathaniel t expanded the business to include financial services in  the bank of n t butterfield was founded as bermudas first bank butterfield was incorporated by an act of parliament in bermuda in  in  during world war ii the bank opened a branch in st georges bermuda to serve military personnel following the war the bank experienced rapid growth increasing its number of shareholders by  and thus becoming the largest bermuda company in terms of shareholders during the s the bank opened branches in the united kingdom and the cayman islands and formed new companies to handle mortgages and trusts followed by its third bermuda branch in somerset bermuda in  during the s the bank took over the bermuda national bank expanded its overseas business and introduced automated teller machines atms into bermuda in  the bank acquired city of london merchant bank leopold joseph this purchase also included leopold joseph guernsey limited in march  butterfield group posted a us million loss and announced that cibc the carlyle group and other institutional investors had collectively purchased a majority stake in the bank through a capital injection of us million it was also announced at that time that ceo  president alan thompson had stepped down from leadership of the company with thencfo brad kopp assuming the role of president  ceo butterfield returned to profitability in  posting net income for the year of us million in  brendan mcdonagh who was previously chief executive officer of hsbc north america holdings and group managing director hsbc holdings plc joined butterfield as a director and executive chairman in august  mr mcdonagh was named chairman and chief executive officer in  butterfield acquired the trust and fiduciary services business of guernseybased legis group adding further scale to its international trust business in  butterfield completed the acquisition of select personal and corporate banking business from hsbc in the cayman islands similarly expanding its market presence in that market on april   butterfield repurchased and cancelled the majority of cibcs shareholding in the bank with other shareholders taking up cibcs remaining shares and cibc ceased to be a butterfield shareholder in september  michael collins who was previously senior executive vice president was named butterfields chief executive officer brendan mcdonagh former ceo became the banks executive chairman mcdonagh retired from the bank and board in october  at which time barclay simmons previously vice chairman became chairman of the board in february  butterfield announced that it had commenced an orderly wind down of its deposit taking and investment management businesses in the uk the bank intends to utilize the capital that was deployed to the uk operations to support the development of other businesses within the butterfield group butterfield is an official supplier and has been named official bermuda bank of the  americas cup which is being held in bermuda referencesedit  bank of nt butterfield  son limited bermuda stock exchange  archived from the original on  retrieved    cibc takes minority stake in bermuda bank the globe and mail toronto   external linksedit butterfield group website butterfield group our history annual reports v t e commercial and retail banks in the united kingdom banking in the united kingdom barclays barclays bank barclays wealth cybg clydesdale bank yorkshire bank hsbc holdings first direct hsbc bank hsbc private bank ms bank lloyds banking group bank of scotland bank of wales birmingham midshires halifax lloyds bank royal bank of scotland group adam and company child  co coutts  co drummonds bank natwest royal bank of scotland ulster bank isle of man bank santander group cahoot cater allen santander uk wholly stateowned national savings and investments uk financial investments uk asset resolution bradford  bingley nram other al rayan bank aldermore allied irish bank gb first trust bank arbuthnot latham  co secure trust bank bank and clients bank of ireland butterfield bank cambridge  counties bank c hoare  co close brothers group the cooperative bank smile danske bank duncan lawrie handelsbanken harrods bank julian hodge bank kingdom bank kleinwort hambros metro bank monzo onesavings bank post office money raphaels bank reliance bank n m rothschild  sons sainsburys bank shawbrook bank standard chartered tesco bank triodos bank tsb unity trust bank virgin money big four banks are underlined and private banks are shown in italics   owned by ukfi  mortgage assets only v t e the carlyle group william e conway jr daniel a daniello david rubenstein aerospace defense arinc asiasat combined systems dhs technologies sequa wesco aircraft transportation allison transmission diversified machine inc hertz metaldyne trenstar unite